@alexandermcqueen unveils the lookbook for its latest FW21 collection shot by HYPEBEAST. With a focus on exaggerated silhouettes, bold volumes and clean lines the winter offering features an array of outerwear, denim and sweaters as well as formal suits. A range of footwear combining the brand’s signature use of fine materials, craftsmanship and functional design also serve as stand-out additions. To round off the collection is a series of “McQueen Graffiti Sunglasses” arriving in a variety of colored lenses inspired by the street art scene.

@hypebeastcarclub: ⁠Just 1,311 @ferrari F40s were built between 1987 and 1992, and now this rare, blue example has just sold for approximately $1,368,000 USD. Starting life in Nyon near Lake Geneva in 1989, this model was taken to Japan in 2004 and was converted into the F40 LM by Liberty Walk. Since then, the Liberty Walk-bodied car exchanged multiple hands until it was finally brought back to the U.K. and was returned to its original condition, and painted blue. Hit the link in bio to learn more.⁠⁠
Photo: Sam Moores/The Market by Bonhams

@hypebeaststyle: @arcteryxnewyork has unveiled one of its more recent upcycling initiatives: a collaboration with @kumanokoido — a made-to-order teddy bear brand. The duo has created a collection of bears that are each repurposed from damaged Arc’teryx Alpha SV Jackets. Each handmade take varies between red and black bases, with some featuring toggles or zippers, before being finished with Arc’teryx embroidery. While the unique bears are not for sale to the general public, they’re currently on display from the Arc’teryx Flatiron location in NYC.⁠⁠
Photo: Nayquan Shuler
